data.title: Comedian Chelsea Handler Coming to Minnesota, Iowa
data.meta_description: Shows are in May and December
data.text:
Grammy Award nominee Chelsea Handler is bringing her stand-up comedy to the Tri-State area for a pair of shows in 2024.

Handler's The LBB (Little Big Bitch) Tour will play in Minnesota this month and in Iowa in December.

The Minnesota stop is Friday, May 24, at Mystic Lake Casino Hotel in Prior Lake.

The Iowa stop is Thursday, December 5, at the Des Moines Civic Center.

Handler, a native of Livingston, New Jersey, is the former host of Chelsea Lately on the E! network (2007-14) and later released a documentary series, Chelsea Does, on Netflix in January 2016. From 2016 to 2017, she hosted the talk show Chelsea on Netflix.

She got her start in television in 2002 on the Oxygen series Girls Behaving Badly. She later appeared on Weekends at the D.L., The Bernie Mac Show, My Wife and Kids, and The Practice. Handler was also a regular on The Tonight Show.

[brandedappromo]

In 2007, she was a member of Comedy Central's Hour Stand-Up Comedy Tour.

Handler has also written six books over the years, including 2008's Are You There, Vodka?, which was the inspiration for the NBC sitcom Are You There, Chelsea? which ran from January to March, 2012.

That same year, Handler was named one of the 100 most influential people in the world by Time magazine.

In 2021, she was nominated for a Grammy for her comedy album Evolution. She lost to Louis C.K.'s Sincerely.
